1
00:00:17,879 --> 00:00:19,399
Driver, take me to Xingfu Village.

2
00:01:07,239 --> 00:01:08,480
This is what you call betrayal.

3
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:19,439
Liu Xiang and I were like real sisters.

4
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:21,480
I urged her many times over the years

5
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,760
to leave Feng Bing.

6
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,680
Feng Bing had been abusing her.

7
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,959
But she just couldn't bring herself to.

8
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:33,079
Sis.

9
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,799
Why can't you make up your mind to leave that monster?

10
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,760
Do you still have hope for him?

11
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:41,519
We fell in love back in college.

12
00:01:42,319 --> 00:01:44,280
Then I got pregnant and we got married.

13
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:48,000
Before we married, he was always good to me.

14
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,040
Basically, whatever I asked for,

15
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,959
he'd find a way to give me.

16
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:55,519
The kindness he showed while courting you

17
00:01:55,799 --> 00:01:59,239
was actually emotional manipulation through giving.

18
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,359
It was his perfect disguise during courtship.

19
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,920
So... wasn't that love?

20
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:07,959
Sis.

21
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,960
Feng Bing is a textbook narcissist.

22
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,319
The extreme devotion he showed during courtship

23
00:02:14,319 --> 00:02:16,000
didn't come from true love.

24
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:18,520
It was through this so-called perfection

25
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:21,400
that he fed his narcissistic need to be needed.

26
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,840
In his mind, you're just his property.

27
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:26,840
All that early devotion

28
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:29,000
was just to smoothly secure ownership.

29
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,479
We're discussing something so serious.

30
00:02:33,479 --> 00:02:34,479
What are you smiling about?

31
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,879
I should give you some credit.

32
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:40,080
In just one year,

33
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,599
you've learned so much.

34
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:43,319
All because of you.

35
00:02:44,479 --> 00:02:45,360
Let me tell you,

36
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,319
for your sake,

37
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:48,879
my bank job's almost become my side gig.

38
00:02:49,319 --> 00:02:51,960
I even got certified as a counselor.

39
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,280
So when it comes to emotional issues,

40
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,439
you have to listen to me.

41
00:02:58,919 --> 00:03:01,120
Is there really no way to save it?

42
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,280
People like him are beyond saving.

43
00:03:03,639 --> 00:03:04,439
His true colors

44
00:03:04,439 --> 00:03:06,520
came out shortly after the marriage.

45
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:09,800
Because he thinks you completely belong to him,

46
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,120
he started getting worse.

47
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:14,719
Controlling your ties with friends and family,

48
00:03:15,479 --> 00:03:16,759
exploiting your soft heart,

49
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,360
repeatedly promising to change,

50
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:21,080
finally pushing you into total isolation,

51
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,479
so you'd have no one to rely on but him.

52
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:26,319
I know his photo studio isn't doing well.

53
00:03:26,759 --> 00:03:28,520
He's wanted a new camera for a while.

54
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,759
I found a shop with installment plans

55
00:03:31,759 --> 00:03:32,879
and ordered one for him.

56
00:03:33,719 --> 00:03:35,039
I've been paying for months.

57
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,439
It'll arrive any day now.

58
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,400
I want to use his birthday

59
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,719
to surprise him.

60
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,039
Sis.

61
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:45,159
You're only hurting yourself this way.

62
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,360
Qing.

63
00:03:50,639 --> 00:03:52,599
Let me try just one last time.

64
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:02,080
Impossible. No, impossible!

65
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,800
You're lying to me! You're lying!

66
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,439
You're lying! It can't be!

67
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,159
Feng Bing.

68
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,199
Shen Qing told us all of this herself.

69
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:11,599
You didn't just kill Liu Xiang with your own hands,

70
00:04:13,199 --> 00:04:14,319
you also killed yourself.

71
00:04:27,319 --> 00:04:28,120
Boss.

72
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,759
Why are there so many evil people in this world?

73
00:04:31,199 --> 00:04:32,480
I went way too easy on him just now.

74
00:04:33,519 --> 00:04:34,680
Once you've worked more cases,

75
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:35,879
you won't ask that question anymore.

76
00:04:36,319 --> 00:04:38,519
Evil doesn't only exist in extreme cases.

77
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,439
It usually exists in small forms in everyday life.

78
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,639
Murder and arson are evil,

79
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,839
but isn't being an enabler just as evil?

80
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,480
That's why we detectives

81
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:52,360
exist to fight evil.

82
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,560
I'll drag every evil hiding in the dark

83
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,360
out into the light.

84
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,160
Jiang Han, remember this.

85
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,040
We hunt evil

86
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,040
and fight evil

87
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:02,560
not to prove how terrible this world is,

88
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,759
but so that more good people

89
00:05:05,759 --> 00:05:07,120
can live their lives in peace.

90
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,480
Got it?

91
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:12,399
Yeah.

92
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,600
How's your driving?

93
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:14,680
Not bad.

94
00:05:15,199 --> 00:05:16,160
You're driving from now on.

95
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,600
Ruo Lan.

96
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:57,560
Brother Mingliang.

97
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,360
Happy birthday.

98
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,519
Thank you.

99
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:03,120
Brother Mingliang, you actually remembered my birthday.

100
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:04,160
Of course I did.

101
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:05,199
How could I ever forget?

102
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,920
Oh, right.

103
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:12,759
I can't accept this gift.

104
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:13,720
It's way too expensive.

105
00:06:13,839 --> 00:06:16,040
Nonsense. A birthday needs a gift.

106
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,040
Honestly,

107
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,800
you didn't have to come all this way.

108
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:21,839
No, no, I had to.

109
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,279
I have to prove my sincerity through action.

110
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,600
Brother Mingliang.

111
00:06:27,439 --> 00:06:29,199
You really don't have to be this nice to me.

112
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,199
Ruo Lan.

113
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,519
We've known each other for so long now.

114
00:06:35,279 --> 00:06:36,639
Stop treating me like a stranger.

115
00:06:37,279 --> 00:06:38,439
No, no, no, I don't.

116
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:41,079
I've always known you've been really good to me.

117
00:06:41,759 --> 00:06:43,000
You take such good care of me.

118
00:06:43,759 --> 00:06:44,759
And in my heart,

119
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:47,639
I've always seen you as a brother.

120
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,399
A brother?

121
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:51,920
But...

122
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:52,879
But...

123
00:06:53,959 --> 00:06:54,639
Brother Mingliang.

124
00:06:54,759 --> 00:06:56,120
I'm going to be late for work.

125
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:56,800
Ruo Lan.

126
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,399
Um...

127
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,519
Are you free tonight?

128
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,439
I'd like to treat you to a seafood dinner.

129
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,079
And celebrate your birthday properly.

130
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:06,519
I already have plans with my brother tonight.

131
00:07:06,839 --> 00:07:08,639
Maybe... next time?

132
00:07:10,879 --> 00:07:11,920
Next time.

133
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:15,920
I know.

134
00:07:16,319 --> 00:07:17,319
When a girl says

135
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,759
"next time," it really means

136
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:21,800
"goodbye, don't bother."

137
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:28,079
Brother Mingliang.

138
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:30,879
I don't want to hurt you.

139
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,120
Silly girl.

140
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:36,920
You don't really know me.

141
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:41,040
I'm not that easily hurt.

142
00:07:43,639 --> 00:07:44,399
I'm leaving then.

143
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:45,399
Okay, bye.

144
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:47,480
Bye.

145
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,600
Captain Li.

146
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:01,120
Brother Wang and Fang Ping

147
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,879
located the suspect vehicle in Anping Town.

148
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,600
Anping Town?

149
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:26,839
Stop running!

150
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:38,240
Stop!

151
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:39,799
Stop running!

152
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,200
Stop!

153
00:08:45,519 --> 00:08:46,279
Don't move!

154
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,200
Help!

155
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:47,799
Calm down!

156
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:48,399
Help me!

157
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:49,480
Grab my hand!

158
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,080
Boss!

159
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,320
Hang on!

160
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:52,440
Jiang Han!

161
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:53,639
Save him first!

162
00:08:53,639 --> 00:08:54,600
I don't want to die!

163
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,320
Captain Li! Captain Li!

164
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:05,759
Hurry!

165
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:07,879
Why so rough?

166
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,039
Quite the runner, aren't you.

167
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:11,960
I'm innocent!

168
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,360
What happened to your arm?

169
00:09:18,919 --> 00:09:19,720
You're hurt.

170
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,519
Just a scrape, I think.

171
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:24,200
It's nothing.

172
00:09:24,759 --> 00:09:25,840
Come on, to the hospital.

173
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:26,919
No need.

174
00:09:27,399 --> 00:09:28,320
Why go to the hospital?

175
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,320
What a waste of money.

176
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,080
What if you get tetanus?

177
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,080
I'm worried you'll try to extort me.

178
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:34,039
Boss, I did pretty well today, right?

179
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,120
You should at least give me some praise.

180
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:36,919
Treat me to a meal.

181
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,440
Fine, consider yourself praised.

182
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,840
I'll treat you to...

183
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:44,840
wontons.

184
00:09:45,879 --> 00:09:46,399
Seriously?

185
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,679
You built that up just for wontons?

186
00:09:48,679 --> 00:09:49,679
I want hot pot!

187
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:38,720
Come on.

188
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,000
Help me.

189
00:11:44,639 --> 00:11:45,720
You're quite pretty.

190
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,080
Don't.

191
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,720
Please, I'm begging you.

192
00:11:54,039 --> 00:11:54,759
Let go!

193
00:11:55,399 --> 00:11:56,120
Let go!

194
00:11:59,279 --> 00:12:00,840
Do you think the crime you committed

195
00:12:01,399 --> 00:12:03,200
is just a simple hit-and-run?

196
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:05,519
I was going to call for help.

197
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,960
But I'd had too much to drink that day.

198
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:11,080
I couldn't afford it even if I sold everything.

199
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:13,679
The more I thought about it, the more scared I got.

200
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,480
So then I just ran.

201
00:12:16,799 --> 00:12:17,919
I'd advise you to come clean.

202
00:12:18,399 --> 00:12:19,679
Without evidence of your crime,

203
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:20,960
we wouldn't have arrested you.

204
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,159
I've really told you everything.

205
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:25,440
Where did you take the victim?

206
00:12:26,039 --> 00:12:26,960
What?

207
00:12:27,639 --> 00:12:28,960
Playing dumb, are you?

208
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,480
You hit her that badly,

209
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,279
and you still raped her?

210
00:12:32,279 --> 00:12:33,360
Are you even human?

211
00:12:33,639 --> 00:12:34,960
What? Rape?

212
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:37,080
I... I didn't rape her.

213
00:12:39,879 --> 00:12:40,320
I...

214
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:41,639
I... I really didn't do anything.

215
00:12:41,639 --> 00:12:42,480
I just ran away.

216
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,879
Who can vouch for that?

217
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:47,919
A taxi. There was a taxi driver.

218
00:12:47,919 --> 00:12:49,080
He can vouch for me.

219
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,840
He must have seen me hit her.

220
00:12:51,159 --> 00:12:52,679
After he drove past me,

221
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,039
he turned around and came back.

222
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:47,960
A taxi again? Really?

223
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,440
Ruo Lan.

224
00:13:58,279 --> 00:13:58,879
Dr. Meng.

225
00:13:59,759 --> 00:14:01,159
It's getting pretty late.

226
00:14:01,159 --> 00:14:02,399
Why don't I drive you home?

227
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:03,799
No, no, no, that's okay.

228
00:14:03,799 --> 00:14:05,080
My brother already said

229
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,000
he'd pick me up after work.

230
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:06,799
Alright.

231
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,120
Ruo Lan.

232
00:14:10,759 --> 00:14:12,639
Don't worry, I'll lock the door.

233
00:14:16,879 --> 00:14:17,759
Happy birthday.

234
00:14:18,519 --> 00:14:19,320
Thank you so much.

235
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,600
Bye, Dr. Meng.

236
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:58,960
Hello.

237
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,720
The number you have dialed is powered off.

238
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:24,879
Driver, take me to Xingfu Village.

239
00:16:03,519 --> 00:16:04,440
Driver!

240
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,919
I was hit by a car.

241
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,480
To...

242
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:10,440
To the hospital.

243
00:16:34,279 --> 00:16:35,320
This might hurt a little.

244
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,360
I'll be gentle.
